&lt;p&gt;We currently have a full time permanent contract for a Band 5 Staff Nurse on Ward 16 &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Ward 16 is a 12 bedded elective orthopaedic ward caring for patients of all ages who require elective orthopaedic surgery. The post would suit a newly qualified Staff Nurse or an experienced Staff Nurse wanting to gain further experience in orthopaedic nursing. We work within the enhanced recovery program and encourage our patients to get dressed as part of the pjparalysis and mobilise independently&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for someone with good communication skills, who is enthusiastic and motivated to learn. You will be working in a close knit team within a busy ward and we will you require you to be flexible in your hours of working to ensure that we can deliver a quality service. We will offer a full induction into the ward and have a Practice Development Sister who works with the ward to help address any of your current and future development needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDawn HorthJob titleWard ManagerTelephone number01253 953416Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sister Helen Worsley&lt;br /&gt;Tel: 01253 953416&lt;/p&gt;
